Korean People's Day of Victory in War Marked Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held at the building of the Romanian Working Party (RWP) and in London and Kiev from July 23 to 25 on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War.
 Niculae Ion Cristian, general secretary of the RWP, and other speakers said that the victory of the Korean people in the Korean war was a victory of the outstanding commanding art of President  Kim Il Sung and the faith and will of the Korean people and their unbreakable unity to defend the sovereignty and dignity of the country, knit close around him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the national liberation and anti-imperialist struggles raged everywhere in the world, encouraged by the brilliant victory of the Korean people, they stressed that the RWP would voice support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harpal Brar, chairman of the British Friendship Society with Korea, noted that the DPRK is standing as a powerful socialist fortress on the forefront of the anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle. He called on the progressive people and organizations of the world to wage a vigorous movement for solidarizing with the DPRK on various occasions and by diverse means. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gennadi Berdyshev, vice-chairman of the Ukraine-DPRK Friendship Association, said in his speech that the victory of the Korean people in the last Korean war was a victory of Kim Il Sung, the Korean People's Army and the people's power founded by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to leader Kim Jong Il was adopted at a meeting in Ukraine.

Passage of "Bill on Human Rights in North Korea" Flailed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The 33rd Friday Rally for Defending Peace against the U.S. and War was reportedly held in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on July 30 to denounce the U.S. for adopting a "bill on the human rights in north Korea" under the sponsorship of the Headquarters of the Anti-U.S. and Anti-War Movement for Urging the Conclusion of a North-U.S. Non-Aggression Treaty.
 At the rally Kwon O Chang, permanent co-representative of the Solidarity for Implementing the south-north joint declaration, said the U.S., failing to bring the north to its knees by force of arms, is seeking the change of the system in the north by every conceivable base means and method. He branded the bill which was carried through the U.S. House of Representatives some time ago as a strategy for bringing the north to a collapse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwon O Hon, chairman of the Association for Supporting the Prisoners of Conscience under the Family Movement for Realizing Democracy, said the bill is aimed to set the Korean nation at odds and divide it and subject it to the U.S. domination and interference. Therefore, it signifies interference in the internal affairs not only of the north but of our whole nation, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution published at the rally notes that the U.S. scheme to unleash another war of aggression on the Korean peninsula under the pretext of the "human rights problem" of the north is being promoted with a meticulous plan and operation to gain supremacy in Northeast Asia. A struggle will be waged to smash it, states the resolution.

Struggle against Troop Dispatch to Iraq Unabated in South Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A candlelight meeting to decisively check the troop dispatch to Iraq was reportedly held in front of Kwanghwamun in Seoul on July 31 under the sponsorship of the People's Action against Troop Dispatch.
 It was attended by at least 1,500 members of the "National Group of Marchers against the Troop Dispatch to Iraq," the Vanguard for Reunification of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting Han Sang Ryol, permanent representative of the Reunification Solidarity, said that the struggle for the withdrawal of the decision on troop dispatch was a campaign for peace and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 O Jong Ryol, permanent chairman of the south Korean Alliance for Democracy and Reunification, called for taking the struggle as a golden opportunity to decisively break off the south Korea-U.S. alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Song Il, chairman of the Committee for National Reunification of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) who is leader of the Vanguard for Reunification of the South Headquarters of Pomchonghakryon, called for fighting to check the troop dispatch without fail and making 2005 the year of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the group of marchers arrived in Seoul that day and continued their march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was joined by the hunger strikers' group of Hanchongryon, members of civic and public organizations, religionists, former "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army, primary schoolchildren and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The group of marchers held a rally at the plaza in front of Yongdungpho Railway Station and called a press conference in front of the "government" building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the conference strongly demanded the "government authorities" immediately stop the dispatch of an advance party to Iraq, withdraw the decision on additional troop dispatch and pullback of the already-dispatched troops.

Animal Growth Accelerant 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Faculty of Life Science of Kim Il Sung University has developed a new kind of growth accelerant for animals.
 The newly developed accelerant is considered to be better than other kinds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is made of raw materials abundant in the country and its production processes are comparatively simple, so its production cost is very low. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its acceleration rate is 10-15 percent higher than other kinds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It accelerates the growth of animals with a less amount of feed and helps raise their resistance to cold. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It can be easily applied to all livestock. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the elements of the accelerant, with no poisonous effect, are completely dissolved and absorbed in animal body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has already been applied to chicken, duck and other stock farms.

Flame Stand Ready for International Martial Arts Games 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A flame stand for the First International Martial Arts Games has been installed in front of the Taekwon-Do Hall on the Chongchun Street in Pyongyang, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 The granite stand consists of a platform 6 meters both in long and wide, pillars, eaves, props and caldron. The stand is 4.5 meters high and its floor space is 36 square meters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The face of the stand is carved with IMGC (International Martial Arts Games Committee), flanked by staircases leading up to the caldron. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stand, which will represent the history of friendship, unity and grand gathering of martial arts players across the world, will adorn the opening ceremony of the games.

Rodong Sinmun on DPRK-Russia Friendship
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 3rd anniversary of the DPRK-Russia Moscow Declaration which was published while leader Kim Jong Il was paying a historical visit to Russia.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today says Kim Jong Il's visit to Russia and the birth of the declaration were a dramatic event of distinguished significance in the history of DPRK-Russia friendship in the new century, which has made a sizable contribution to guaranteeing peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The author of the article further says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last three years following the publication of the declaration have been days in which the DPRK-Russia friendly relations have made a steady development on a new stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian people are now making strenuous efforts to achieve social stability and national unity and defend the security and interests of the country under the leadership of President V.V. Putin. Affirmative changes are taking place in different fields of social life and economic and defense potentials are growing thanks to measures of the Russian government and the labor of the Russian people. Russia opposes all manner of terrorism and war and it is striving for the guarantee of world peace and security and for a fair and peaceful solution to international issues while seeking the multipolarization of the world. The voice and dignity of Russia are being boosted in the international arena. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people appreciate the efforts of the Russian government and people for social development and defense of the security and interests of the country, sincerely hoping that everything will go favorably in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the invariable will and stand of the Korean people to consistently strengthen and develop DPRK-Russia friendship in response to the requirements of the new century, concludes the article.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work on National Reunification Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Wednesday dedicates a signed article to the 7th anniversary of the publication of leader Kim Jong Il's work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" (August 4,1997).
 The work is an immortal library for national reunification as it lays down all tasks and ways to achieve national reunification, the lifelong cause of President Kim Il Sung, and a great programme for reunification as it indicates the path for the cause of national independence and reunification to follow in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work lucidly sets out the ideas and theories and ways of victoriously leading the movement for reunification, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The master key to national reunification is to preserve and glorify the exploits performed by the President in leading the struggle for reunification and implement to the letter the Juche-oriented line and policy for national reunification put forward by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il in the work formulated the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point program for the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo set forth by the President as three charters for national reunification and clarified his stand that national reunification should be achieved on the basis of these three charters no matter how the situation and circumstances may change. This was a declaration of his unshakable faith and will to carry out the cause of national reunification, true to Kim Il Sung's instructions for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic significance of his work lies in that he encouraged all Koreans replete with the unanimous longing for the President to implement his instructions for reunification and provided them with the master key to bringing about a turning phase in the movement for national independence and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to reunify the country at an early date, true to the instructions of the President for national reunification and Kim Jong Il's idea and leadership over the struggle for reunification, all Koreans should consolidate the great national unity, fully demonstrate its might and escalate the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle and decisively foil all sinister attempts to bring the inter-Korean relations back to those in the era of confrontation, under the uplifted banner of national independence, the article concludes.

Book "In Memory of President Kim Il Sung" Published in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Book "In Memory of President Kim Il Sung" was brought out by the Publishing House of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cooperation with Foreign Countries on the occasion of the 10th anniversary of his demise.
 The four volume book was printed in English, Spanish, French and Russian. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Edited in the book according to different regions are articles written by 43 famous figures of the world and their children who had the honour of being received by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed on the front cover of the first volume titled "The Eternal Sun of Mankind" written by figures of Asia and Oceania is a portrait of the smiling President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It carries 12 articles such as "The Eternal Sun of Mankind" written by Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, "Continued Affection" by Zhang Jinquan, son of Zhang Weihua associated with the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, and "Great Wisdom" by Vessa Burchett, wife of former Australian writer and journalist Wilfred Burchett. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A photograph of the President waving high to the cheering people, his face beaming with a smile, is carried on the front cover of the second volume titled "The Care of the Sun" written by Latin American figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It contains 8 articles including "Calling Me Long-Time Comrade-in-Arms", "Personally Fastening a Wrist Watch around My Wrist" "The Care of the Sun" and "The Great Teacher." They were written by Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli, former general secretary of the Popular Force Organized in Costa Rica, Candelaria Rodriguez, former Cuban woman lawyer, Humberto Ortiz Flores, manager of the "Voluntad" Publishing House of Ecuador, Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen on the front cover of the third volume entitled "His Care Will Last Forever" is a photograph of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the supreme temple of Juche, where the President lies in state. It carries 13 articles written by figures of Africa and Middle East. They include articles entitled "An Hour Spent with the Great Leader" by Magige Nyerere, son of Julius K. Nyerere, former president of Tanzania, "Invincible Fortress" by Mohammed Ibrahim Ali, commander of the People's Army of Syria, and "His Care Will Last Forever" by Emile Tompapa, chairman of the National Information Committee of Guinea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed on the front cover of the last volume titled "Tracing Back Every Unforgettable Event" is a photograph of the statue of the President on Mansu Hill. It has ten articles written by European figures. Among them are articles captioned "President Kim Il Sung Was World Political Elder," "Fatherly Leader of People Who Is Lodestar of the Cause of National Reunification" and "Noble Sense of Obligation" by Paulette Pierson, honorary professor at the Free University of Brussels, Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, Ivan Nobichenko who is son of Ya. T. Nobichenko, an internationalist soldier.

KCNA Dismisses Misinformation Spread by S. Korean "Ministry of Unification"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The "Ministry of Unification" of south Korea posted on its Internet homepage a sheer lie. It claimed that nuclear scientist of the north Kim Kwang Bin, after turning his coat and running away from the north, testified to the fact  that the north developed nukes by use of highly enriched uranium in top secrecy and hid in other places researchers of the existing institute no. 19, nuclear fuel rods and other major facilities while freezing the facilities in Nyongbyon in 1994.
 Kim Kwang Bin whom the ministry painted as the man who sought asylum in a third country is a researcher of merit active at a maritime radioactive research institution of the DPRK. This being a hard fact, the ministry talked such sheer nonsense that Kim, director of institute no. 38, defected from it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We make it clear that there are no such things as institutes nos. 38 and 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean right-wing conservatives have more than once spread such misinformation. Last year they let a rumor afloat that scores of scientists of the north who were doing normal work in their field exiled themselves to other countries and included in those exiles even those who died long ago only to draw public criticism and ridicule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, they are taking much pain to spread such misinformation. This campaign  is aimed at making the much publicized "enriched uranium program" sound plausible though it is a fiction in a bid to escalate international pressure on the north to drop its nuclear activities for a peaceful purpose and invent a pretext to attack it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is that the dishonest forces of south Korea are conducting such smear campaign under the manipulation of the United States in accordance with its scenario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is widely known that persistently peddling the fiction of "enriched uranium program" in a bid to charge the DPRK with the nuclear development, the United States circulated a false rumor about the "transfer of nuclear technology" by a Pakistani scientist and orchestrated even a deceptive drama called "smuggling of uranium hexafluoride". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is intolerable that the U.S. is persisting in such a ridiculous smear campaign, far from drawing a proper lesson from having created a complicated situation by dreaming up the fiction of "enriched uranium program" and sparking a new nuclear crisis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All facts go to prove that the U.S. and other bellicose elements remain unchanged in their moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and their talk about "peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue" and "landmark proposal" is no more than a deceptive ruse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Taking into consideration the fact that the U.S. set afloat a rumor about Iraq's possession of weapons of mass destruction before unleashing the Iraqi war, the DPRK is left with no option but to heighten vigilance against their anti-DPRK moves and take strong countermeasures.
